[assistant] 抽取并记录信息: {"user_identity": "", "user_preference": "", "research_direction": "Critical illness polyneuropathy or myopathy (CIP/CIM)", "filter_requirements": "时间范围：2011年和2013年；排除标准：不满足研究标准的 studies", "rejection_reasons": "", "other_info": "研究主要探讨了Critical illness polyneuropathy or myopathy (CIP/CIM)的干预措施，包括Insulin therapy、Corticosteroids、Early physical therapy和Electrical muscle stimulation。摘要提到有五项试验符合条件，其中两例比较了Insulin therapy和常规治疗，结果显示Insulin therapy减少了CIP/CIM的发生率，并且显著降低了机械通气时间和180天的死亡率。此外，研究还提到了对CIP/CIM患者进行早期康复的潜在益处，但效果有限。最后，研究建议未来需要更大规模的随机对照试验来进一步探索早期康复和电刺激的效果。"}
[assistant] 抽取并记录信息: {"user_identity": "", "user_preference": "", "research_direction": "CIP/CIM", "filter_requirements": "We included all RCTs in humans that compared the efficacy of any treatment used to prevent or reduce the incidence of CIP or CIM as a primary or secondary outcome to placebo, no treatment or a different treatment. Adults (over 18 years) of either sex, admitted to a medical, surgical or mixed ICU.", "rejection_reasons": "", "other_info": "The primary outcome measure was the incidence of CIP/CIM during ICU stay. We extracted this outcome measure in ICU. As no internationally accepted criteria exist for this diagnosis, we defined CIP/CIM for the purpose of this review as weakness of the limbs or respiratory muscles, or as EMG documented peripheral polyneuropathy or myopathy for which causes other than CIP/CIM have been excluded. Secondary outcome measures included clinically relevant consequences from a possible reduction in the incidence of CIP/CIM and also any possible side effects of the therapy. The secondary outcomes are limited by their surrogate nature as outcome measures for CIP/CIM, as they can be influenced by other ICU complications."}
